FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-component and remember this as mtk-component forever.

Create a reusable Web Component named `mtk-component`.

Tech Stack:
- HTML
- SCSS only
- Vanilla JavaScript only
- Modern Material Design UI
- Material Design icons/styles
- Bootstrap 5 MAY ONLY be used for layout utilities/grid
- No frameworks
- No external libraries
- Use this repository as the base: https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website.git
- Use all wc code for include, publish, subscribe etc from this file: https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/blob/main/js/_wc.js

Component Architecture:
- Root element:
  <mtk-component class="mtk-component"></mtk-component>

- Root CSS namespace:
  .mtk-component

- ALL styles MUST be fully scoped to:
  .mtk-component

- NEVER use:
  - global styles
  - global selectors
  - IDs
  - inline styles
  - inline JavaScript
  - iframes

- MUST use:
  <wc-include href="..." />

Configuration:
- Component MUST be fully JSON-driven
- ALL data MUST come from:
  `mtk-component.config.js`

JavaScript Requirements:
- Create a dedicated ES6 class named:
  `MtkComponent`

- Automatically initialize the component inside:
  `mtk-component.js`

- MUST wait for DOM availability because the component will be dynamically injected using:
  `<wc-include>`

Event System:
- Subscribe to:
  `4-mtk-component`
  using:
  `wc.subscribe`

- Create:
  `onMessage(message)`
  handler function

- Publish all click/actions using:
  `wc.publish`

- BEFORE every publish:
  log the payload using:
  `wc.log`

Styling Rules:
- Use styles, colors, spacing, typography, elevation, and motion patterns from:
  `css/nala.scss`

- Use Material Design:
  - floating labels
  - cards
  - buttons
  - focus states
  - transitions
  - accessibility patterns

Accessibility Requirements:
- Semantic HTML only
- ADA compliant
- Keyboard accessible
- Visible focus states
- Proper ARIA usage where appropriate

Code Quality:
- Modular
- Reusable
- Maintainable
- Production-ready
- Mobile responsive
- No duplicated logic

Output Requirements:
Create EXACTLY these files:

- mtk-component.config.js
- mtk-component.scss
- mtk-component.html
- mtk-component.js

DO NOT:
- generate partial snippets
- generate patch files
- generate explanations
- generate markdown code blocks

ONLY generate complete files.

Goal:
Create a reusable, scalable, JSON-driven Material Design Web Component system that integrates with the wc event ecosystem and supports dynamic loading through wc-include.
